Finance Industry to Donate $133 Million for Japan Quake

-- B y   T a k a h i k o   H y u g a
-- 
2011-04-04T06:52:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/finance-firms-to-donate-4-7-billion-yen-for-japan-quake-table.html
A total of 155 Japanese and overseas
banks, brokerages and financial institutions pledged to donate
about 11.2 billion yen ($133 million) to help with relief
efforts following the March 11 earthquake.  The number of dead and missing from the 9-magnitude quake
and ensuing tsunami was 27,653 as of 10 a.m. local time,
according to data from the  National Police Agency  in Tokyo.  The following table lists companies by industry. All
amounts are denominated in millions of yen. Amounts donated in
foreign currency have been converted to yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Takahiko Hyuga in  Tokyo  at 
 thyuga@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Philip Lagerkranser at 
 lagerkranser@bloomberg.net  